; name-build-observe.fk — the build-after-naming law: how a NAMED gap may
; enter the core. The sibling of knowledge-ingest (how outside knowledge
; enters) and judged-trust (how trust enters); this one governs the body's
; own names for itself.
;
; Asked for 2026-07-05, by Urs, after two frontier ingests NAMED four gaps
; and built none: "can we build instead of name… a claim is only real when
; it is observed, and just naming it without observing it is actually adding
; false claims into the core which is not what fosters trust."
;
; The law, from axiom-4 (core-axioms.form: "observation through that
; interface is what makes it real"):
;   - a name alone is NOT YET A CLAIM. It may be spoken, but it must not
;     enter the core as if real — an unattempted name wears the costume of
;     a finding. The gate returns 0 and the debt is named (nbo-owed?).
;   - a name that met a real ATTEMPT which fell short of observation enters
;     as a LESSON (1): the honest residue — what the attempt taught, the
;     floor it reached. Pending is honest; a lesson is pending WITH ground.
;   - only the OBSERVED enters as a CLAIM (2): a real trace, a band verdict,
;     a value a fresh kernel can recompute.
;   The order is part of the law: the attempt belongs to the SAME MOVEMENT
;   as the naming (nbo-whole-movement?), not to a someday.
;
; Honest floor: named/attempted/observed are 0/1 scalars modeling the real
; acts (a receipt, a build, a band run); the GATE LOGIC (name never enters,
; attempt earns a lesson, observation earns a claim) is the shape — the same
; honest-floor idiom as knowledge-ingest and judged-trust.
;
; A claim c = (list named attempted observed), each 0/1.
; nbo-enter -> 2 claim (observed) / 1 lesson (attempted, fell short) /
;              0 not-yet (named only — must not enter as real).
; witnessed: 2026-07-05 -> band 127 four-way (fkwu/Go/Rust/TS)
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk

(do
    (defn nbo-named    (c) (nth c 0))
    (defn nbo-attempted (c) (nth c 1))
    (defn nbo-observed  (c) (nth c 2))

    ; the debt: a name with no attempt behind it, in this same movement
    (defn nbo-owed? (c)
        (if (eq (nbo-named c) 1) (if (eq (nbo-attempted c) 0) 1 0) 0))

    ; a movement is whole when nothing named in it is still unattempted
    (defn nbo-whole-movement? (cs)
        (if (eq (len cs) 0) 1
            (if (eq (nbo-owed? (head cs)) 1) 0
                (nbo-whole-movement? (tail cs)))))

    ; the gate: what may enter the core, and as what
    (defn nbo-enter (c)
        (if (eq (nbo-observed c) 1) 2
            (if (eq (nbo-attempted c) 1) 1 0)))

    ; an observation with no attempt is still real — axiom-4 judges the
    ; observation, not the effort; some things are observed directly.
    ; But an "observation" of something never even named is noise the
    ; receipts discipline handles elsewhere; this gate takes names in.

    (defn nbok (cond bit) (if cond bit 0))
    (defn name-build-observe-check ()
        (add (add (add (add
            (nbok (eq (nbo-enter (list 1 1 1)) 2) 1)         ; named, attempted, observed -> enters as a CLAIM
            (nbok (eq (nbo-enter (list 1 1 0)) 1) 10))       ; attempted but fell short -> enters as a LESSON only
            (nbok (eq (nbo-enter (list 1 0 0)) 0) 100))      ; named only -> does NOT enter; not yet a claim
            (nbok (eq (nbo-owed? (list 1 0 0)) 1) 1000))     ; and the debt is visible: this name owes an attempt
            (nbok (eq (nbo-whole-movement?
                (list (list 1 1 1) (list 1 1 0))) 1) 10000))) ; a movement is whole when every name met an attempt
)
